        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-08-13T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-08-13T14:00:00-05:00" n="399" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d399">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 P.W. (Peace)/8–1347: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Political Adviser in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-08-13T15:00:00-04:00">August 13, 1947—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>319. For Atcheson. As Dept is undertaking basic review of overall factors
                    involved in Jap peace settlement hope you can have detailed discussion with
                    Supreme Commander before your departure in order that we may have benefit of his
                    views on both short and long range objectives for Japan and its place in overall
                    Far East and world picture.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
